         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/8/81. ¶  ¶ Since I wrote to you, dear Sir Joseph, I have received from King George's Sound ¶  dried plants, corresponding to the species of Andersonia, transmitted to you in the Wardian Case. ¶   ¶...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.08.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, ff. 315-16.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26/8/81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since I wrote to you, dear Sir Joseph, I have received from King George's Sound<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
               </note> dried plants, corresponding to the species of Andersonia, transmitted to you in the Wardian Case.<seg style="font-size: 8pt; "> </seg>I find however, that my order was only improperly carried out, in as much as two species only with <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">blue</hi>
               </seg> corolla were sent, namely A. caerulea &amp; A. depressa, and that instead of A. variegata, which is the third species (unless also A. micrantha) with blue corollas, my collector sent you <name key="Andersonia%20homalostoma">Andersonia homalostoma</name>, which latter has both calyx &amp; corolla pink. However as the A. homalostoma is also new for British-culture, I hope it will not come amiss.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 12 July 1881 and notes thereto. The plants all arrived dead.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust you will <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">figure</hi>
               </seg> the two blue-flowered ones, after all the trouble &amp; expense to which I have been put in this affair. If you consider, that out of about 300 <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name> hitherto known, only 3 or perhaps 4 have blue corollas, and if you bear in mind, how rare the blue is in flowers of <name key="Ericeae">Ericeae</name>, then you will be glad to bring this aberration of color (of the purest blue) readily &amp; prominently under notice through your Magazine.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kindly return the Ward's Case filled with some rare plants to me, such as I can grow before the little cottage, where I am compelled to do my officework.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As the freight has been paid by me for this sending to Kew, perhaps you will kindly arrange for the free return-sending of the Wards Case also.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">A. depressa, as you will see, has the calyx nearly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">white</hi>
               </seg>, not pink as in most others. The case was shipped by the P &amp; O Steamer from K G Sound early in August. I have no bill of Loading; so kindly let the Kew Agent <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">look out</hi>
               </seg> for the Case. The Chief Officer of the Steamer, who deserves some compliment from you, took <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">particular</hi>
               </seg> care in giving the case a good place.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andersonia%20caerulea">Andersonia caerulea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andersonia%20depressa">Andersonia depressa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andersonia%20homalostoma">Andersonia homalostoma</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andersonia%20micrantha">Andersonia micrantha</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Andersonia%20variegata">Andersonia variegata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ericeae">Ericeae</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
